    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Independence Study for CFD Hemolysis Solver",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry to assess discretization error. Three mesh densities (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.3M cells) were evaluated at the nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3500 RPM). Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude at 12 monitor points. The fine mesh was selected for production runs based on GCI < 2% criterion.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementStudy",
